<TITLE> Charge framing in Babar tax-dodge case on Mar 11 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 2 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court has set March 11 to frame charges against detained former state minister for home Lutfozzaman Babar in a tax evasion case. Senior special judge ANM Bashirullah set the date on Tuesday. He also sent the case to Dhaka Special Judge's Court-5, additional public prosecutor Shah Alam Talukder told bdnews24.com. The National Board of Revenue filed the case against Babar on Feb 14. The case statement says the former state minister, as a director of Master Electronics Industry Limited, concealed income of around Tk 8.6 crore in 1999-2000 and 2008-2009 tax years and evaded the tax counted on it. Babar is currently behind bars serving 17 years in an arms case. He has also been shown arrested in the Aug 2004 grenade attack case and the Kibria murder case. b
